{
  "id": "61e91b386bf112001df5f238",
  "title": "(3.3) Memory becomes strong by repeated use",
  "created": 1549694164,
  "updated": 1553590957,
  "lines": [
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e0000786ffb",
      "text": "(3.3) Memory becomes strong by repeated use",
      "created": 1549694164,
      "updated": 1553590937,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e0000786ffc",
      "text": "We learned that memory and [muscle] are similar. Then, what is the difference? In memory, there is a phase of \"[memorization]\" that inputs information and a phase of \"[recall]\" that outputs information. Something different happens in these two phases, such as the occurrence of a [theta wave] of 4 to 12 Hz in the hippocampus only in the phase of the memorization.",
      "created": 1549695970,
      "updated": 1549696122,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e0000786ffd",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1549695970,
      "updated": 1549695970,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e0000786ffe",
      "text": "When thinking about repeating something for memory, people tend to imagine repeating input, but both are necessary. ",
      "created": 1549695970,
      "updated": 1549695976,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e0000786fff",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1549695970,
      "updated": 1549695970,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e0000787000",
      "text": "When similar information repeatedly enters the brain, the brain gets slower and duller and finally ignores the information. *15",
      "created": 1549695970,
      "updated": 1549695970,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e0000787001",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1549695970,
      "updated": 1549695970,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e0000787002",
      "text": "This mechanism is for ignoring useless information. It is similar to getting bored if you repeat similar tasks. *16",
      "created": 1549695970,
      "updated": 1549695970,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e0000787003",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1549695970,
      "updated": 1549695990,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e0000787004",
      "text": "What is \"useful\" information for the brain? That related to [reward]. If you do not get rewards such as achievement, pleasure, or joy, your brain behaves as if that information is useless and ignores them.",
      "created": 1549695970,
      "updated": 1549696006,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e0000787005",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1549695970,
      "updated": 1549695970,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e0000787006",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1549695970,
      "updated": 1549695970,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e0000787007",
      "text": "Repetition of input only tends to be boring. It is necessary to repeat including the output. And it is even better if you earn rewards for the output.",
      "created": 1549695970,
      "updated": 1549695970,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e0000787008",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1549695970,
      "updated": 1549695970,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e0000787009",
      "text": "---",
      "created": 1553590950,
      "updated": 1553590952,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e000078700a",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1553590957,
      "updated": 1553590957,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e000078700b",
      "text": "Footnotes:",
      "created": 1553590952,
      "updated": 1553590955,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e000078700c",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1553590955,
      "updated": 1553590955,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e000078700d",
      "text": " *15 It is called \"[habituation].\"",
      "created": 1549695970,
      "updated": 1553590949,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e000078700e",
      "text": " *16 This story is just an analogy. Phenomena in one neuron and phenomenon in the whole human are not the same.",
      "created": 1549695970,
      "updated": 1553590949,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e000078700f",
      "text": "[en.icon]",
      "created": 1553590957,
      "updated": 1553590957,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    }
  ]
}